Add a public function called PrintDictionary to Collections.calr that iterates over a dictionary and prints each key-value pair. The function takes a Dictionary<string, int> parameter and returns void.

Use this exact Calor foreach-kv syntax:
§F{f001:PrintDictionary:pub}
  §I{Dictionary<str,i32>:dict}
  §O{void}
  §E{cw}
  §EACHKV{e001:k:v} dict
    §C{Console.WriteLine}
      §A k
    §/C
    §C{Console.WriteLine}
      §A v
    §/C
  §/EACHKV{e001}
§/F{f001}

The §EACHKV{id:keyVar:valueVar} collection syntax creates a foreach loop for key-value pairs where:
- id is a unique loop identifier (e001)
- keyVar is the variable name for the key (k)
- valueVar is the variable name for the value (v)
- collection is the dictionary to iterate
